-- Amazon Taken Offline as Hackers Launch Cyber Attack, Telegraph Reports
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2010-12-13T03:23:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/amazon-taken-offline-as-hackers-launch-attack-telegraph-reports.html
(Corrects originating newspaper.)  Amazon.com Inc., the U.S.-based
online shopping site, was shut down for a time last night in
several countries, with hackers blamed for the disruption, the
Daily Telegraph reported, Activists protesting against actions
taken in opposition to WikiLeaks are believed to be responsible
for the shutdown, the Telegraph said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
